<title>FRANCE: Fire at hotel in central France kills four.</title>
<headline>Fire at hotel in central France kills four.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1996-08-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>A fire gutted a hotel in central France on Wednesday morning, killing four people and injuring about a dozen others, officials said.</p>
<p>Flames spread rapidly up a lift shaft in the small Le Savoy hotel in Clermont-Ferrand, trapping many guests in their rooms on the upper floors.</p>
<p>The cause of the fire, which began around 2 a.m. (midnight GMT), was unknown. The victims were mostly students or workers, all apparently French citizens.</p>
